    -#%p
    -#  %u
    -#    Your Express Consent to Collection and Use of Information.
    -#  %span
    -#    If you do not agree with any disclosure in this Privacy Policy, or have any questions, please do not access the Site or provide any personal information; instead, contact us directly at ContractOfficer@htri.net, and we will be pleased to assist. BY CHOOSING TO PROCEED AND ACCESS THE SITE OR OTHERWISE PROVIDING PERSONAL INFORMATION YOU ARE INDICATING YOUR EXPRESS CONSENT AND AGREEMENT TO THE COLLECTION, TRANSFER, HANDLING, PROCESSING, USE, AND STORAGE OF PERSONAL INFORMATION PURSUANT TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY. You grant HTRI and any third party referenced in this Privacy Policy a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free perpetual, unless revoked by you in writing, license to use your personal information for the purposes mentioned in this policy.
    -#
    -#Exclusive Disclosures Pertaining to Use of Personal Information. This Privacy Policy covers information you provide to us via this Site, via use of HTRI products and services that connect to this Site, or otherwise communicate to us, and does not alter or affect the terms and conditions of any other agreement you may have or enter into with HTRI for any given product or service.
    -#
    -#Personal Information We Collect.
    -#
    -#A. Information You Give Us
    -#
    -#We may collect certain information about you and your use of the Site using tracking technologies or other passive means to help us improve our products and your experience when accessing our Site. We also may ask you to submit personal information such as your address, job title, and work phone number to verify your company affiliation; your client’s names, addresses and other contact details in order to perform the purpose for which the information is provided.  We may also collect information to comply with government regulations. Once you provide us with personal information about you or your clients, you are no longer anonymous to us. This information may include:
    -#
    -#Booking information: You may be required to provide personal information so we can provide hotel booking services via the Site.
    -#
    -#Additional Information: Additional information you provide to us may include your feedback, messages, emails, and answers to surveys or questionnaires that you may submit, as well as any contact information you provide in order to receive updates from us.
    -#
    -#B. Location Information.
    -#
    -#We may collect your IP address, which could provide us with general information about your location.
    -#
    -#C. Automated Information Collection
    -#
    -#Automated information collection includes “passively collected” information that is, but not limited to, identifying product information, the domain name of the website that allowed you to navigate to the Site, search engines used, the internet protocol (IP) address used, the length of time spent on the Site, the pages you looked at on the Site, other websites you visited before and after visiting the Site, the type of internet browser you have, the frequency of your visits to the Site, and other relevant statistics, including the following:
    -#
    -#Log Information. When you access the Site, our servers automatically record information that your browser sends whenever you visit a website. These server logs may include information such as your web request, IP address, browser type, browser language, the date and time of your request, your computer operating system, mobile device and mobile operating system, name of your internet service provider or your mobile carrier, and one or more cookies (small text files containing a string of characters) that may uniquely identify your browser.
    -#
    -#Links. The Site may include links in a format that enables us to keep track of whether these links have been followed by IP addresses. We use this information to improve the quality of our Site and Services.
    -#
    -#Location Information. We may receive location data passed to us from location-enabled devices or that you have enabled, from your browser, or from third party services.
    -#Product Information.  When you use HTRI products we may collect information that identifies the specific product you are using, such as the software name, version number, and serial number.
    -#
    -#URLs. When you visit or access the Site, we automatically receive the URL of the site from which you came and the site to which you are going when you leave the Site. Additionally, advertisers receive the URL of the page you were on when you click on an ad on the Site.
    -#
    -#Cookies. Part of our data collection process may involve the use of "cookies," which are small pieces of identifying information placed and stored on your computer by our server, which enable our system to more readily "recognize" you when you visit. Cookies are frequently used to enable sites to more efficiently provide service, such as to customize the display to suit your interests, note your interests while visiting our Site, and store information. It is our policy that any information obtained through the use of cookies will only be used internally by HTRI to better provide service to you and to evaluate and improve the effectiveness of the Site. Cookies will not be used to track your activities outside of the Site or for any purpose not disclosed herein. You may elect not to accept "cookies" by setting your Internet options on your computer, however, please be advised that in that case, you may not be able to access part or all of this Site, or parts of this Site may not operate effectively.
    -#
    -#Web Beacons. Web beacons (also known as “pixel tags” or “clear GIFs”) are 1x1 single-pixel graphics that allow us to count the number of users who have visited or accessed the Site and to recognize users by accessing our cookies. We may employ web beacons to facilitate Site administration and navigation, to track the actions of users of the Site, to compile aggregate statistics about Site usage and response rates, and to provide an enhanced online experience for visitors to the Site. We may also include web beacons in HTML-formatted email messages that we send to determine which email messages were opened.
    -#
    -#Aggregate Information. We may compile certain personal information and other information collected through the Site on an aggregate basis. This information may include, without limitation, the number of people who have visited the Site and other user demographics. Such aggregate information does not identify you individually.
    -#
    -#How We Use Your Information.
    -#
    -#We may use personal information to provide you with the requested information, goods, services, or materials, for data analysis, to send you updates and news concerning HTRI and its business partners, and better assist you with any future requirements.
    -#
    -#It is our policy not to disclose, sell, or market your personal information to any unaffiliated third party without your prior permission. However, we may transfer or disclose your information to our staff, partners, contractors, and suppliers, subject to use as outlined in this policy.
    -#
    -#
    -#We may disclose your information to any person, specifically to any governmental agency, without notice, if we in good faith believe that such is required in order to comply with law, to protect HTRI interests including this Site, and in response to any emergency situation.
    -#
    -#We may share personal information in accordance with any consent you provide.
    -#
    -#How You May Review and Correct Your Collected Personal Information. You can always choose whether or not to provide information on the Site. However, without the information, we may not be able to provide you some products and services. You may contact us at any time at ContractOfficer@htri.net requesting to review your personal information, if any, which we may have collected, and request that your personal information be corrected, supplemented, or permanently deleted from our systems.
    -#
    -#No Warranties. We employ reasonable security precautions to help protect against the loss, misuse, and alteration of personal information provided on or through the Site. Due to the numerous technical and operational uncertainties, we cannot make any warranty, guarantee or representation concerning the accuracy, thoroughness, completeness, or currency of your information, nor over our ability to control, correct, access, handle, process, use, store or transfer such information, and all such warranties are hereby disclaimed.
    -#
    -#Protection of Your Personal Information. While we strive to undertake appropriate and reasonable measures to safeguard your information, please remember that, due to the many technical uncertainties, complete security of Internet transmissions cannot be guaranteed. Therefore, you understand and agree that HTRI is unable to provide any warranty, guarantee, or representation concerning the protection of your information or concerning the existence or effectiveness of any security measures undertaken. HTRI will not be liable for any claims, losses, or damages resulting from access by an unauthorized third party, or the introduction of viruses, worms, or other harmful elements into the system and their possible effects on personal information contained on the Site.
    -#
    -#Data Protection Directive. The Site is currently hosted in the United States but that may change without notice to you. You have the right to obtain certain information about the processing of your personal data through a Subject Access Request (as defined in the Data Protection Act 1998) by emailing us at GDPR@htri.net. In circumstances where the processing of your personal data is not in compliance with applicable national data protection laws, you may also request rectification, erasure, or blocking of your personal data. We will not keep or process your personal data for longer than is necessary. However, if we retain your personal data, we will continue to keep it in accordance with any applicable statutory or professional retention periods.
    -#
    -#We transfer personal data to third parties using secure methods. For purposes of this clause, “transfers of personal data" means any sharing of personal data by us with a third party, including but not limited to the following:
